Hi, everybody! This is Alexander.

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Today we'd like to present you
this video review of

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.000
the Audio-Technica AT2050 microphone.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:19.000
The condenser microphone AT2050 is an ideal
solution for live performances, 

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
as well as for studio recording of
the vocals, keyboards, strings, 

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:27.000
drums, guitar combos and so on.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
The AT2050 has three switchable
pickup patterns:

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
omnidirectional, cardioid and 8-shape.

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:39.000
The dual large gold-vaporized diaphragm

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:43.000
achieves optimum characteristics
over years of use.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
The AT2050 is able to withstand
a high level of sound pressure

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:51.000
and it has a low self-noise level,

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.000
that helps to achieve a smooth,
natural sound.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
The microphone complies with all standards
of quality and reliability,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:04.000
has a switchable built-in
80Hz high-pass filter,

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
attenuator -10dB,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.000
frequency response from 20 Hz to 20 000 Hz,

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.000
requiers phantom power 11-52V.

